    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_polkinghorne_324509",
        "quote": "Theologians have a great problem because they're seeking to speak about God. Since God is the ground of everything that is, there's a sense in which every human inquiry is grist to the theological mill. Obviously, no theologian can know everything.",
